  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is designed to evaluate the safety, tolerability, pharmacodynamics and
      pharmacokinetics of riociguat at age-, sex- and body-weight-adjusted doses of 0.5 mg, 1.0
      mg, 1.5 mg, 2.0 mg and 2.5 mg TID in children from ≥6 to less than 18 years with pulmonary
      arterial hypertension (PAH) group 1. The study consists of two phases: titration phase up to
      8 weeks and a maintenance phase up to 16 weeks.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
